	abstract = {To know the fertile period and the ovulation, 33 cycles (22-35 days) were studied by means of ovarian ultrasound and urinary LH, enzyme immunoassay of oestrone glucuronide (E1G), and urinary pregnandiol (PdG) with Brown Ovarian Monitor. A mean increase of 1 ml/day in the follicular volume from 3 days before to the ovulation was found. The follicular rupture with a gradual emptiness (2-3 hours) was observed in two cases. The was an ovulatory alternation of 67%. The average period of the follicular phase was from 9 to 19 days (14 ± 0,3) and the average period in the luteal phase moved from 11 to 17 days (14 ± 0,3). The increase of E1G (starting point of fertility) took place from 6 to 3 days before the ovulation day with an average of 5 days (114 ± 6 hours). The ovulation happened in the following 48 hours after E1G peak (an average of 14 ± 4 hours). The increase of PdG (starting point of postovulatory infertility: "cut-off") took place 2-3 days postovulation (average of 66 ± 3 hours). We conclude that the Ovarian Monitor is useful to know the fertile period and the ovulation in women, therefore the ovarian ultrasound states precisely the ovulation day.},
